      • getGrade

        public java.lang.String getGrade(double mark)
        Parameters:
        mark -
        Returns:
        the grade corresponding to the mark passed as the parameter The grade conditions are: marks less than 50: Grade is "F" marks more than or equal to 50 and less than 65: Grade is "P" marks more than or equal to 65 and less than 75: Grade is "Cr" marks more than or equal to 75 and less than 85: Grade is "D" marks more than or equal to 85: Grade is "HD"

      • getGrades

        public java.lang.String[] getGrades()
        Returns:
        an array containing the grades this semester in the order of marks. For example, if marks = {76.2, 56, 67.9, 91.3}, the method should return the array {"D", "F", "Cr", "HD"}; (you can use getGrade to get each individual grade)
